  "prompt": "If you open a microwave oven before the beep will it release deadly microwave radiation?",
  "response": "No, opening a microwave oven before the beep will not release deadly microwave radiation. Microwave ovens are designed with safety features to prevent the emission of microwaves when the door is open. These appliances have interlock systems that stop the generation of microwaves as soon as the door is opened. Therefore, it is safe to open the microwave before it beeps, and there is no risk of exposure to harmful microwave radiation.",
